ly</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Interesting spells I want to see</span><hr size=1> I don't really expect mages to out nuke wizards. That is not in our area of expertise. Our power comes from the elementals as well as the ability to summon various things to aid in our fight. Rather than join the I-Can-Nuke-Better-Than-You game, I say lets lobby for things that we mages can do best. Summoning thing is what really makes me happy to play a mage. <br>
<br>
Spells that I would like to see in the upcoming expansion:<br>
<br>
Group Call of the Hero<br>
Mana Cost: 1000 - 1500<br>
Cast Time: 15-18 sec.<br>
Desc: Summons everyone in the party to the magician. CoH is one of our most prized spells. <br>
<br>
Note: In the hands of a smart mage, it has saved the life of the puller/cleric countless times. I have saved my party countless times from wipeout by CoHing the cleric out of harm's way when he/she is being plummeled by a monster due to heal aggro.<br>
<br>
Summon Elemental Plate/Leather/Chain<br>
Mana Cost: 200 - 300<br>
Cast Time: 5 - 6 sec.<br>
Desc: Summon a full set (8 pieces) of plate mail/Chainmail/Leather with plus resistance stat on it. (+3 to +5 on each piece)<br>
<br>
Note: To be usable by both player/pets.<br>
<br>
Rod of Mystical Tranvergance II<br>
Mana Cost: 500 - 600<br>
Cast Time: 6 - 7 sec<br>
Desc: Give 350 mana for 350 health. (Wooo 1 on 1 ratio) 3 Charges.<br>
<br>
Summon Focus items for 61 - 65<br>
Mana cost: 300 - 400<br>
Cast Time: 5 - 6 sec<br>
Desc: More focus items that gives 30% increase in spells for 61-65 spells. (Rings, Bracers, Necklace, Earring, Shoulder)<br>
<br>
Summon Ring/Shard of the Eagle<br>
Mana cost: 200 - 250<br>
Cast Time: 5 - 6 sec<br>
Desc: Summons a ring or ammo item which have unlimited See invisible, Levitation, Ultravision when worn.<br>
<br>
